# UCLA Student API

This API provides endpoints to manage and interact with a database of students. It is built using .NET Core and connects to a PostgreSQL database for storing student data.

## Features
- **Retrieve all students**: Get a list of all students in the database.
- **Add a new student**: Insert new students into the database.
- **Update student details**: Modify an existing student's information.
- **Delete a student**: Remove a student from the database.
- **volume build-in so that you don't lose data even if the container crash**
## Prerequisites
- Docker
- .NET 6.0 or higher
- PostgreSQL database
- Dapper ORM


# Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/ucla-student-api.git
cd ucla-student-api

# you can run the container by doing (be sure to be in the right directory)
docker-compose up --build -d

# in order to reset the volume and the container you can always do this 
docker-compose down -v
docker-compose up --build
